Subject: WiFi is no longer a viable secure connection

Global Secure Systems has said that a Russian's firm's use of the latest
NVidia graphics cards to accelerate WiFi 'password recovery' times by up to
an astonishing 10,000 per cent proves that WiFi's WPA and WPA2 encryption
systems are no longer enough to protect wireless data.

http://www.scmagazineuk.com/WiFi-is-no-longer-a-viable-secure-connection/article/119294/

